Citation.sAbstract: The densities and viscosities of binary mixtures of paraldehyde + propylene carbonate have been measured at (288.15, 293.15, 298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K. From these measurements, excess molar volumes (VE) and viscosity deviations (??) were calculated. These results were fit to a Redlich-Kister polynomial. The results were discussed in terms of molecular interactions.
Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities of Binary Mixtures of Paraldehyde + Propylene Carbonate at (288.15, 293.15, 298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K
